# 2. 新しいクラスで

Teacher: That's it for this homeroom.
Teacher: Next, we have the opening ceremony. Please make sure to be there on time.
Classmates: That was quick. We have a little time before the ceremony begins.
Classmates: Then, let's go see what the other classes are up to! I wanna introduce you to some of my other friends!
Classmates: Yeah, let's go!
Honami: *Sigh* New classrooms always make me feel a little anxious...
Ichika: I kind of know what you mean. The view outside looks completely different.
Ichika: Oh, come to think of it... Aside from us, our class also includes...
Kohane: Ichika! Honami!
Honami: Oh, Kohane...! Does this mean we're in the same class this year?
Kohane: Yeah, and I couldn't be happier. I'm really looking forward to this upcoming year.
Ichika: I think we are as well.
Honami: Wait, Kohane... Have you been a bit short on sleep lately?
Ichika: Huh?
Kohane: Oh...
Kohane: Our team has been practicing a lot recently. We stayed out pretty late last night too. That might be why...
Honami: I see...
Ichika: Your team's practices have always seemed really tough, but does this mean you're practicing even harder now?
Kohane: We are. The practice regimens An's dad put together for us are so tough, but we've been managing...
Honami: That sounds really difficult...
Kohane: It is, and I feel exhausted at the end of each day. But...
Kohane: I feel motivated to keep trying no matter what.
Kohane: What we're after... We know surpassing it won't be easy...
Kohane: But I don't care how hard the road up ahead is. I'm going to do my absolute best and leave no regrets.
Ichika: That's really cool, Kohane...
Kohane: Huh?
Ichika: How do I put it...? You've always been hardworking, but you sound really strong now...
Honami: I agree. Your resolve to keep persevering sounded ironclad.
Kohane: Really...? Hehe. Now I feel a little embarrassed.
Honami: So, Kohane, good luck. We'll be rooting for you!
Kohane: *Nod* Thanks!
Kohane: Oh, before I forget to ask... Which classes are Shiho and Saki in?
Honami: They're both in Class B.
Honami: I know. We have a little time on our hands before the opening ceremony starts, so why don't we go see them?
Ichika: Good call. Everyone else seems to be doing the same thing...
Kohane: Oh, sorry... The teacher actually just asked me to help with something. I need to head over to the office soon.
Honami: Oh, I see. Well, we can always go see them some other time.
Kohane: Yeah, let's!
Ichika: Let's see. Saki and Shiho should be...
Honami: Oh...!
Emu: So! Here's to us being placed in the same class!
Emu: Let's make our second year also really wonderhoy!!!
Saki: Wonderhoy!!!
Shiho: *Sigh*
Emu: Hehe. I'm suuuper duper happy about us becoming classmates!
Emu: We're gonna have so much fun together!
Saki: Yeah! Oh, I know! We should make Print Stickers together sometime!
Emu: Great idea! It's always so much fun to doodle on them and stuff♪ Oh, and I wanna play some games together after!
Saki: Yeah, I like it! We could even follow up with a karaoke place, then have parfaits and...
Shiho: Wait, all in one day?
Shiho: Besides, we work and have band practice. We don't have much time to be playing around.
Saki: O-Oh, right...!
Saki: Oh, Emu, that reminds me... You guys are gonna start visiting a bunch of different venues and troupes, right?
Emu: Yup! We had a long discussion about it, and decided we're gonna go to as many places as we can!
Emu: We're uhh...! Training together to make our dreams come true!
Shiho: Training...?
Emu: Yeah, so I might not have as much time to hang out moving forward...
Emu: But we're in the same class now, so I wanna spend at least a little time together!
Saki: Just a little bit! Pleeease, Shiho!
Shiho: Whoa...
Shiho: Fine, just a little...
Emu & Saki: Woohoo!!!
Miku: <It's kind of funny how powerless Shiho is when it comes to those two.>
Honami: Hehe. Yes, it is.
Saki: Oh, Ichi, Hona!
Shiho: Are you here to see us?
Emu: Hi, everyone! Come on in!!!
Honami: Hehe. I didn't know that you were also in Class B, Emu.
Emu: Yup! I'm a little sad we're not together again...
Emu: But let's keep hanging out like we always have!
Honami: Of course. We can even draw with Ena or spend more time with Mizuki and Ms. Yoisaki.
???: Oh! Hi, everyone!!!
Ichika: Wait, that voice...!
